rgerlichen Moral. So widerlegt gerade die deutsche Lyrik der Epoche eindrucksvoll das lang gehegte Vorurteil, die Aufklärung sei ein 'Zeitalter ohne Poesie'.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aEnlightenment. 0aGerman poetryxHistory and criticism. 0aLyric poetryxHistory and criticism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Literary and Cultural Studies - 1990 - 1999z9783110637830oZDB-23-GLC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-DITION: BEST OF GERMAN STUDIESz9783110233933oZDB-23-DGH0 cprintz978348410556040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311094207140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110942071423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110942071/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGH  aZDB-23-GLCc1990d1999